<!DOCTYPE ui:UiBinder SYSTEM "http://dl.google.com/gwt/DTD/xhtml.ent">
<ui:UiBinder xmlns:ui="urn:ui:com.google.gwt.uibinder" xmlns:g="urn:import:com.google.gwt.user.client.ui">

    <ui:style>
        a {
            color: #03899C;
        }
        
        a:hover {
            color: #1F6B75;
        }
        
        ul.about {
            list-style-type: circle;
        }
        
        ul.about>li {
            padding-left: 20px;
        }
    </ui:style>

    <g:HTML>
        <h1>About</h1>
        <p>
            Waitara (
            <a href="http://www.maoridictionary.co.nz/index.cfm?dictionaryKeywords=task">Maori for "Task"</a>
            ) is a demo task manager
            for an article in
            <a href="http://www.sigs-datacom.de/fachzeitschriften/javaspektrum.html">JavaSPEKTRUM</a>
            written by
            <a href="http://harald.pehl.name">Harald Pehl</a>
            .
        </p>
        <p>
            Waitara uses the following tools and libraries:
        </p>
        <ul class="{style.about}">
            <li>
                <a href="http://code.google.com/intl/de-DE/webtoolkit/overview.html">GWT</a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="http://code.google.com/p/gwt-platform/">GWTP</a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="http://code.google.com/p/google-gin/">GIN</a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="http://code.google.com/p/piriti">Piriti</a>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <p>Through the use of MVP Waitara supports different platforms (desktop, tablet and smartphones). In this
            context as much code as possible is reused and as little code as needed is written per platform.</p>
    </g:HTML>

</ui:UiBinder> 